You are tasked with analyzing order and customer data to build executive "board slides" for a fictional startup food delivery service using Python and Matplotlib.
The main goals and components of the project require you to:
Load and inspect datasets: 
Use Pandas to read provided .csv files containing customer orders, restaurant demographics, and delivery metrics.
Calculate key metrics: Determine business metrics like average order value, total orders by neighborhood, and restaurant ratings.
Recreate graphs using Matplotlib: Build clear visual aids such as pie charts (to show cuisine popularity) and bar charts (to compare restaurant categories and delivery times).
Format as "Board Slides": Compile your charts and insights into a format suitable for a startup executive meeting
